Defendant in custody.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety;
2) Have no contact with Michelle Vandegrift and Paula Scheer;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Have no direct contact or any 3rd party contact with any of the victims unless approved by the agent;
5) Have no contact with any known drug dealers or users;
6) Obtain a high school diploma or its equivalent;
7) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
8) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
9) Pay court costs;
10) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
11) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
12) Write letters or apology to all victims (to be approved by the agent);
13) Spend twelve (12) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing immediately.
